# Public hostname for the service. Use a real subdomain (recommended) whose DNS
# A record points at this VM's public IP — e.g. paxdei.erech.fi. Caddy obtains
# and auto-renews a Let's Encrypt cert for it via the HTTP-01 challenge, so ports
# 80 and 443 must be reachable and DNS must already resolve to the VM (see
# DEPLOY.md). For a quick test before you have a domain, a sslip.io/nip.io name
# embedding the IP also works (e.g. 129-151-221-127.sslip.io).
paxdei.erech.fi {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8787
}
